This paper discusses the emergence of compositional languages in deep learning systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models in multi-agent systems, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of deep learning models in reasoning on an abstract level, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of software development (cs.SD) and neural networks (cs.NE).
